programDescriptions.description:
The California Tourism Market Act provides for the marketing of California through an assessment of businesses that benefit
from travel and tourism. The objective of the Tourism Assessment Program is to identify potentially assessable businesses,
assist companies with determining the appropriate amount of their self-assessment, and collet the fee.

